class="comment-content"><p>Do you know of any ways to substitute the eggs, dairy, and gluten in this pie for those with food allergies? That would make my dreams come true. (I know that making the meringue without eggs may prove to be impossible, but I thought that I may as well ask).</p></div><div
class="comment-reply-link"><a
rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2008/06/frozen-chocolate-truffle-pie/?replytocom=25188#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-25188", "25188", "respond", "1612")'>Reply</a></div></li><li
id="comment-25190" class="comment c53 byuser comment-author-drook bypostauthor c-y2009 c-m08 c-d11 c-h14 depth-1"><div
class="comment-author vcard"><img
alt='' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1a18d426338d4b707ab1d2f4e037af39?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=PG' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span
class="fn n"><a
href='http://cooklikeyourgrandmother.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url url'>Drew</a></span></div><div
class="comment-meta">Posted August 11, 2009 at 2:40 pm <span
class="meta-sep">|</span> <a
href="#comment-25190" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div><div
class="comment-content"><p>Wow, eggs, dairy <em>and</em> gluten? That&#39;s a tough one.</p><p>For the crust, I&#39;d change completely to something like the <a
href="http://blog.cooklikeyourgrandmother.com/2009/04/how-to-make-graham-cracker-crust.html" rel="nofollow">graham cracker crust</a>, but made with gluten-free crackers.</p><p>But there&#39;s a <em>lot</em> of butter and eggs in the filling. Once I&#39;m substituting more than half the ingredients in a recipe, I start to think I&#39;d be better off starting from a different recipe.</p><p>If I <em>had to</em> try it though &#8230; I&#39;d replace the egg yolks with the equivalent volume crushed banana for richness. All I can find for the meringue is <a
href="http://www.recipe4living.com/articles/food_allergies_and_how_to_deal.htm" rel="nofollow">this quote</a>: &quot;As a substitute for whipped eggs, as in meringue recipes, let 1/4 tsp. xanthan gum and 1/4 C. water stand until thickened and whip like egg whites.&quot;</p><p>For the butter, in most pastry recipes you can substitute lard for butter (and vice-versa), but I don&#39;t think that would work here. I hate to recommend margarine, but when you&#39;re dealing with an allergy it may be the lesser of two evils.</p></div><div
