id="comment-25311" class="comment c56 byuser comment-author-drook bypostauthor c-y2009 c-m08 c-d22 c-h19 alt depth-1"><div
class="comment-author vcard"><img
alt='' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1a18d426338d4b707ab1d2f4e037af39?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=PG' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span
class="fn n"><a
href='http://cooklikeyourgrandmother.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url url'>Drew</a></span></div><div
class="comment-meta">Posted August 22, 2009 at 7:51 pm <span
class="meta-sep">|</span> <a
href="#comment-25311" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div><div
class="comment-content"><p>No, I&#39;m not cooking the eggs. And plenty of people will have a fit about that.</p><p>The real recommendation from scientists who have studied it is that the elderly, the very young, and those with compromised immune systems should avoid raw eggs. But &quot;just to be on the safe side&quot; &#8212; which is code for &quot;It&#39;s easier to have a simple rule that&#39;s wrong, than a complex rule that&#39;s right&quot; &#8212; that gets turned into &quot;never eat raw eggs&quot;.</p></div><div
class="comment-reply-link"><a
rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2008/06/frozen-chocolate-truffle-pie/?replytocom=25311#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-25311", "25311", "respond", "1612")'>Reply</a></div></li><li
